│── frontend/         # HTML/CSS/JavaScript files for UI  
│── test/             # Smart contract tests  
│── hardhat.config.js # Hardhat configuration file  
│── package.json      # Dependencies and scripts  
⚙️ Installation & Setup
1️⃣ Clone the Repository
bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/lavisha25/Blockchain-Certificate-Generator.git
cd Blockchain-Certificate-Generator
2️⃣ Install Dependencies
bash
Copy
Edit
npm install
3️⃣ Start Local Blockchain
bash
Copy
Edit
npx hardhat node
💡 Keep this terminal running — it’s your local Ethereum network.

4️⃣ Deploy Smart Contract
Open a new terminal in the same folder:

bash
Copy
Edit
npx hardhat run scripts/deploy.js --network localhost
5️⃣ Start Frontend
Go inside the frontend folder and open index.html in your browser.

💡 You must have MetaMask installed and connected to the local network.

🚀 How to Use
Issuer Login → Connect wallet → Enter certificate details → Click Issue Certificate.

Verification → Enter the certificate ID → Click Verify to check authenticity.

📦 Requirements
Node.js (v16 or above)

MetaMask browser extension

Hardhat (comes with the project)

🛠 Tech Stack
Solidity – Smart contracts

Hardhat – Development framework

Ethers.js – Blockchain communication

HTML/CSS/JavaScript – Frontend

MetaMask – Wallet integration

